Scala supports XML *literals*.  Meaning that this program:

<script src="http://gist.github.com/154847.js"></script>

outputs this:

.pre <html>
  <head>
    <title>Hello Literals!</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>Literals are handy</h1>
    <p>
      They keep you from having to using <a href="http://www.unnecessaryquotes.com/">unnecessary quotes</a>.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
